    "This class of distribution accounts for over-dispersion and low sensitivity which are inherent to blood-based genomic and transcriptomic measurements (Supplementary Figure 1ac).",
    "It has a two-arm architecture, modeling the expression of oncRNAs in one arm and the expression of annotated smRNAs in the other.",
    "The latter is used to account for differences in the size of sequencing libraries across samples.",
    "Orion also includes additional classification and contrastive learning objectives to accommodate label prediction and remove unwanted confounders in the learned representations (Figure 1b).",
